The Firm
Executive search defined by depth, not volume.

Bound was founded on a conviction most firms get wrong: recruiting is not a transaction. Every engagement is retained, personally led, and grounded in genuine understanding of the client’s business, culture, and competitive landscape.

Founded in Philadelphia, serving manufacturers nationwide. Bound works with industrial companies, PE-backed portfolio businesses, and the organizations that power the real economy.

Our Methodology

AI insights, delivered by humans,
for an incredibly personalized search.

01
Machine Scale

AI-Powered Intelligence

Proprietary AI tools map the full universe of qualified candidates — not just those in databases. Market mapping, compensation benchmarking, and competitive intelligence at a scale no human team can replicate.

02
Human Judgment

Human Curation

Every candidate is personally vetted for technical capability, cultural alignment, and leadership trajectory. No algorithmic shortlists. No resume blasts. Every conversation is substantive.

03
Adaptive

Client Partnership

Real-time access to a dedicated consultant — not a portal. The process adapts to each search, each culture, each hire. No playbook is one-size-fits-all.

04
Accountable

Placement & Beyond

Offer negotiation, counteroffer strategy, resignation coaching, and 90-day onboarding support. Ends when the hire is performing — not when the offer is signed.

The Founder

Bob Cwenar

Bob Cwenar brings over a decade of retained executive search experience to every engagement. A graduate of Drexel University, he began his career with Armstrong Franklin, growing the practice from a four-person startup into a recognized name in the industry.

Through a merger with GattiHR and subsequent acquisition by Kingsley Gate Partners, Bob led national searches for clients ranging from agile startups to enterprises exceeding $10 billion in revenue.

Today, Bob leads Bound Search Partners with a clear mandate: deliver an executive search experience defined by rigor, precision, and trust.
